pipeline_summary.name: WF_MAIN_DATASETS_LOAD_L2_TO_L2
pipeline_summary.description: Comprehensive pipeline that orchestrates dataset loading from DWH L2 to L2 with segmentation processing and SAP integration.

components.name: Wait for L2 Full Load Flag
components.description: Polls the md.dwh_flag table in the DWH until the 'l1_to_l2_load_successfull' flag for the previous business day is set.
outputs: Sensor release signal to downstream tasks

components.name: Generate Load Identifier
components.description: Creates a unique load identifier for the workflow and pushes it via XCom for downstream consumption.

components.name: Register Workflow Session
components.description: Registers a new workflow session in the metadata system using the generated load identifier.
outputs: session registration records in metadata tables

components.name: Wait for Previous Day End Task
components.description: Monitors the external DAG 'WF_MAIN_DATASETS_LOAD_L2_TO_L2' for successful completion of its 'end' task from the previous day.
outputs: Sensor release signal to downstream tasks

components.name: Trigger PostgreSQL Session Cleanup
components.description: Triggers the external DAG 'sys_kill_all_session_pg' to clean up PostgreSQL sessions before parallel execution.

components.name: Trigger Reporting Data Preparation
components.description: Triggers the external DAG 'wf_data_preparation_for_reports' to prepare reporting datasets after session cleanup.

components.name: Trigger Client Segmentation Load
components.description: Triggers the external DAG 'l1_to_l2_p_load_data_ds_client_segmentation_full' to load client segmentation data.
outputs: Trigger of client segmentation load DAG

components.name: Notify SAP of Segmentation Completion
components.description: Sends an HTTP POST to the SAP system indicating successful client segmentation data load.
inputs: Completion of client segmentation load DAG

components.name: Finalize Workflow
components.description: Updates metadata tables to mark the workflow session as successful after both parallel branches complete.
outputs: Workflow session status updated in metadata tables

upstream_policy.description: Runs after both parallel branches (reporting preparation and SAP notification) succeed

components.name: Send Failure Notification Email
components.description: Sends an email to configured recipients if any upstream task in the pipeline fails.
inputs: Failure signals from any upstream task

upstream_policy.description: Triggered when any upstream task fails (trigger_rule='one_failed')

description.default: Comprehensive pipeline that orchestrates dataset loading from DWH L2 to L2 with segmentation processing and SAP integration.

trigger_dag_id.description: ID of the DAG to trigger for session cleanup

wait_for_completion.description: Whether to wait for the triggered DAG to finish

pool.description: Pool name to limit concurrent runs

pool_slots.description: Number of slots to consume from the pool

trigger_dag_id.description: ID of the DAG to trigger for client segmentation load

recipients.description: Email addresses to notify on failure

sources: md.dwh_flag table in the PostgreSQL DWH (flag indicating previous day's L1L2 load success)
Previous day's execution status of external DAG 'WF_MAIN_DATASETS_LOAD_L2_TO_L2' (end task)
Client segmentation source data residing in wk_export.ds_client_segmentation_last_v (used by downstream segmentation load)
sinks: SAP system  HTTP POST flag indicating successful client segmentation load
Metadata tables in the DWH (workflow session and status records)
Failure notification email sent via SMTP
